00:04:34.230 --> 00:04:35.130
the right idea.

00:04:35.130 --> 00:04:37.880
It's got a modern-looking UI.

00:04:37.880 --> 00:04:39.450
It's kind of hollowish.

00:04:39.450 --> 00:04:40.580
It's not quite hollow.

00:04:40.580 --> 00:04:42.450
It's not quite an action bar.

00:04:42.450 --> 00:04:43.770
And that's one of the things
which I really want to

00:04:43.770 --> 00:04:47.480
highlight for these guys-- is
you can see in particular on

00:04:47.480 --> 00:04:50.340
the pseudo action bar that
they've got along the bottom,

00:04:50.340 --> 00:04:52.000
the alignment isn't
quite right.

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:55.080
So they've got the overflow
icon that looks right.

00:04:55.080 --> 00:04:56.650
But it's not quite in
the right place.

00:04:56.650 --> 00:04:59.740
And so you really want to think
about if you're going to

00:04:59.740 --> 00:05:04.530
use some of the common UI
paradigms within the platform,

00:05:04.530 --> 00:05:06.350
it's really important to use
them in a way that's

00:05:06.350 --> 00:05:10.740
consistent with other apps using
the same controls-- the

00:05:10.740 --> 00:05:11.780
same paradigms.

00:05:11.780 --> 00:05:13.550
Where it really gets confusing
is if it's something that

00:05:13.550 --> 00:05:17.210
looks kind of like something
that you're expecting but

00:05:17.210 --> 00:05:19.320
doesn't quite work
in the same way.

00:05:19.320 --> 00:05:21.560
It produces slightly different
results or is laid out

00:05:21.560 --> 00:05:22.640
slightly differently.

00:05:22.640 --> 00:05:23.970
That just causes confusion.

00:05:23.970 --> 00:05:26.240
So you're almost better off
doing something completely

00:05:26.240 --> 00:05:29.820
unique if you want to do any
sort of significant variance

00:05:29.820 --> 00:05:33.010
on one of the existing
UI pieces.

00:05:33.010 --> 00:05:35.870
Similarly, we've got the little
icon on the bottom

00:05:35.870 --> 00:05:38.070
right, which is kind of cute.

00:05:38.070 --> 00:05:41.150
But it actually just adds
visual clutter.

00:05:41.150 --> 00:05:43.760
And you can actually see it says
"Home" there, which is

00:05:43.760 --> 00:05:47.170
actually, I think, a description
of where you are

00:05:47.170 --> 00:05:47.920
within the app.

00:05:47.920 --> 00:05:49.490
Either way, it's kind
of confusing.

00:05:49.490 --> 00:05:50.460
Because is it clickable?

00:05:50.460 --> 00:05:50.950
Is it not?

00:05:50.950 --> 00:05:52.370
Is it a navigation prompt?

00:05:52.370 --> 00:05:54.770
Or is it just decoration?

00:05:54.770 --> 00:05:57.620
You really want to try and keep
your screen as clean and

00:05:57.620 --> 00:05:58.540
clear as possible.

00:05:58.540 --> 00:06:01.320
Now, I'm not going to go into
too much detail on the UI

00:06:01.320 --> 00:06:04.300
because that's kind of Android
design and actions territory.

00:06:04.300 --> 00:06:07.150
And I don't want to step
on their toes too much.

00:06:07.150 --> 00:06:09.760
But if we switch to
the giant phone--

00:06:09.760 --> 00:06:12.130
if we're really lucky, the giant
phone will be working--

00:06:12.130 --> 00:06:13.950
excellent--

00:06:13.950 --> 00:06:15.110
so you can see, they've
got this

00:06:15.110 --> 00:06:17.910
distinctive UI on the screen.

00:06:17.910 --> 00:06:20.980
It's got this bright green--
almost sort of similar sort of

00:06:20.980 --> 00:06:24.460
coloring to HTC Sense's UI from
at least a couple years

00:06:24.460 --> 00:06:26.310
ago when I last looked at it.

00:06:26.310 --> 00:06:28.200
You've got sort of the
pseudo action bar

00:06:28.200 --> 00:06:29.510
here along the bottom.

00:06:29.510 --> 00:06:32.980
And they've sort of put the time
in that as well, which

00:06:32.980 --> 00:06:33.740
make sense.

00:06:33.740 --> 00:06:35.680
But it's also kind of redundant
because I have the

00:06:35.680 --> 00:06:38.550
time on the top of my phone
up here as well.

00:06:38.550 --> 00:06:41.750
So it's kind of like
I'd rather see the

00:06:41.750 --> 00:06:44.030
overflow menu here--

00:06:44.030 --> 00:06:46.440
down along the bottom here where
it should be-- where it

00:06:46.440 --> 00:06:48.080
kind of belongs on Android.

00:06:48.080 --> 00:06:50.280
Otherwise, it just makes
it a bit confusing.

00:06:50.280 --> 00:06:52.450
Otherwise, what we've got
here along the bottom is

00:06:52.450 --> 00:06:53.940
effectively your tab.

00:06:53.940 --> 00:06:55.245
So each of these--

00:06:55.245 --> 00:06:57.260
and again, this is a little bit
confusing because we've

00:06:57.260 --> 00:07:00.150
combined the concepts of an
action with the concepts of

00:07:00.150 --> 00:07:00.830
navigation.

00:07:00.830 --> 00:07:05.920
So things like hitting the moon
button effectively puts

00:07:05.920 --> 00:07:07.250
you to sleep.

00:07:07.250 --> 00:07:08.660
So that's an action--
fair enough.

00:07:08.660 --> 00:07:13.480
But hitting the bar brings up
the activity for being able to

00:07:13.480 --> 00:07:15.170
monitor your previous sleeps.

00:07:15.170 --> 00:07:17.130
And so it's gets a little
bit confusing.

00:07:17.130 --> 00:07:18.200
Because what's an action?

00:07:18.200 --> 00:07:18.905
What's a navigation?

00:07:18.905 --> 00:07:21.930
It should be a little easier,
particularly for users.

00:07:21.930 --> 00:07:25.060
You want to make sure users know
what to expect whenever

00:07:25.060 --> 00:07:27.430
they're pressing something
on your UI--

00:07:27.430 --> 00:07:29.550
so making that a little
more predictable--

00:07:29.550 --> 00:07:32.570
perhaps using something
similar to Android.

00:07:32.570 --> 00:07:35.490
And in particular in this
layout, they've used something

00:07:35.490 --> 00:07:38.780
that looks like in action bar,
but it almost feels like

00:07:38.780 --> 00:07:39.920
they're trying to cheat.

00:07:39.920 --> 00:07:43.430
So one of the big pieces of
feedback we often have is that

00:07:43.430 --> 00:07:45.930
you're not supposed to have
tabs along the bottom.

00:07:45.930 --> 00:07:48.040
And I'm sure the explanation
here is,

00:07:48.040 --> 00:07:49.050
well, they're not tabs--

00:07:49.050 --> 00:07:49.260
right?

00:07:49.260 --> 00:07:50.010
It's an action bar.

00:07:50.010 --> 00:07:52.080
You're allowed to have an action
bar along the bottom.

00:07:52.080 --> 00:07:52.540
And it's true.

00:07:52.540 --> 00:07:53.460
You are.

00:07:53.460 --> 00:07:57.440
But only as sort of the second
half of a split action bar.

00:07:57.440 --> 00:07:59.550
And we don't have anything
along the top here.

00:07:59.550 --> 00:08:02.300
So I'd much rather like to see
this flipped around so that

00:08:02.300 --> 00:08:04.310
the action bar sits
on the top.

00:08:04.310 --> 00:08:05.720
You've got navigation
on the left.

00:08:05.720 --> 00:08:07.920
You've got actions on the right.
and it's a lot clearer

00:08:07.920 --> 00:08:12.130
as to exactly how it all
is supposed to work.

00:08:12.130 --> 00:08:14.130
So here, again, we go through.

00:08:14.130 --> 00:08:15.720
You hit plus.

00:08:15.720 --> 00:08:19.250
It lets you set an alarm as to
when you want to wake up.

00:08:19.250 --> 00:08:23.500
Or you can just have a
nap, which is nice.

00:08:23.500 --> 00:08:26.430
So I'm not going to go into too
much detail on the UI in

00:08:26.430 --> 00:08:27.320
the interest of time.

00:08:27.320 --> 00:08:33.010
But kind of the key is here when
you press the Go button.

00:08:33.010 --> 00:08:35.659
And it's going to start
recording my sleep.

00:08:35.659 --> 00:08:37.700
And it's going to use a variety
of senses in order to

00:08:37.700 --> 00:08:40.049
do that and give me an
indication of how good a

00:08:40.049 --> 00:08:44.000
night's sleep I have,
which is nice.

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:45.440
That's basically the
whole purpose.

00:08:45.440 --> 00:08:48.310
But what I think is kind of,
again, confusing here is that

00:08:48.310 --> 00:08:52.800
we have an overflow icon, which
I'm covering slightly.

00:08:52.800 --> 00:08:57.420
So you've got this overflow
icon and sort of

00:08:57.420 --> 00:08:58.410
unpredictable behavior.

00:08:58.410 --> 00:09:02.090
So if I click this, it's going
to bring up sort of this

00:09:02.090 --> 00:09:06.000
contextual menu bar, which is
not really what I'm expecting.

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:08.690
It's kind of a dialogue where
I'm expecting a pop-up

00:09:08.690 --> 00:09:09.940
overflow menu.

00:09:12.070 --> 00:09:13.840
The things which we've
got here to set

00:09:13.840 --> 00:09:14.570
are all fair enough.

00:09:14.570 --> 00:09:16.920
It's just, again, the
way that it behaved.

00:09:16.920 --> 00:09:18.720
And if we leave this screen long
enough, it'll all turn

00:09:18.720 --> 00:09:21.160
off and go dark, which
again is nice.

00:09:21.160 --> 00:09:22.910
So you can see here--
dimming screen--

00:09:22.910 --> 00:09:25.340
touch-- or back to return.

00:09:25.340 --> 00:09:27.000
And so this is good because
it means that the

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:27.900
phone can stay on.

00:09:27.900 --> 00:09:30.100
And if it wants to use senses,
it's going to have to stay

00:09:30.100 --> 00:09:32.250
active while I'm asleep.

00:09:32.250 --> 00:09:34.470
So it's really important
here that it does

00:09:34.470 --> 00:09:36.880
this, which is nice.

00:09:36.880 --> 00:09:38.760
We hit Back and it automatically
records

00:09:38.760 --> 00:09:42.150
everything, which is good.

00:09:42.150 --> 00:09:44.265
So otherwise, it works well.

00:09:44.265 --> 00:09:45.760
It does what it's
intended to do.

00:09:45.760 --> 00:09:49.170
But I think really the key for
this app is all about tweaking

00:09:49.170 --> 00:09:51.740
the UI-- making the navigation
and the actions a little bit

00:09:51.740 --> 00:09:53.890
easier-- a little bit
more obvious.

00:09:53.890 --> 00:09:56.700
Otherwise, great information
around statistics--

00:09:56.700 --> 00:09:57.820
well displayed, as well.

00:09:57.820 --> 00:10:00.610
I really like the use of graphs
and tables to try and

00:10:00.610 --> 00:10:03.885
make this information as easily
consumed as possible.

